name: WebHistoryItem
desc: WebHistoryItem objects encapsulate information about visiting a page so that users can return to that page. WebHistory and WebBackForwardList objects manage lists of WebHistoryItem objects. WebHistoryItem objects are created and added to these lists automatically when loading pages, so you do not need to create WebHistoryItem objects directly.

items.name: init!(urlString: String!, title: String!, lastVisitedTimeInterval: TimeInterval)
items.desc: Initializes the receiver with a URL,URLString, a title specified by title and the last time this item was visited specified by time title, and time last visited.

items.name: var urlString: String!
items.desc: The string representation of the URL for the receiver’s page.

items.name: var originalURLString: String!
items.desc: The string representation of the original URL for the receiver’s page.

items.name: var alternateTitle: String!
items.desc: An alternate title that may be used in place of the receiver’s page title.

items.name: var icon: NSImage!
items.desc: The icon for the receiver’s page, or nil if none exists.

items.name: var lastVisitedTimeInterval: TimeInterval
items.desc: The last time and date the receiver’s page was visited.

items.name: static let WebHistoryItemChanged: NSNotification.Name
items.desc: Posted by a WebHistoryItem object when the value of the history item’s title, alternate title, URL strings, or last visited interval changes.
